Helen Eugenia Parker (1909-c.1940) bụ onye Amerịka na-ese ụkpụrụ ụlọ.

A mụrụ Parker na onye ọrụ ngo Walter Eugene Parker na Willie Parker na Pine Bluff, Arkansas na 17 Nọvemba afọ 1909. Ezinụlọ asaa mechara kwaga Little Rock, Arkansas. Mgbe ọ gụsịrị akwụkwọ n'afọ 1926 na Wiley High School-College na Marshall, Texas (nke a maara dị ka Wiley College taa), ọ bụ nwa akwụkwọ kachasị elu. O yikarịrị ka ọ gara Mahadum Howard na Washington, D.C.
Parker laghachiri na Little Rock n'oge na-adịghị anya
N'ebe ahụ, ọ kụziri mgbakọ na mwepụ na ụlọ akwụkwọ sekọndrị ọha na eze, jere ozi dị ka onye na-elekọta ọbá akwụkwọ na ọbá akwụkwọ a na-ekewapụ, ma na-agakwuru Southern Tenant Farmers Union.

N'ihe dị ka afọ 1930, Parker kwagara Detroit, Michigan. N'ebe ahụ, ọ bụ onye nkuzi maka Shop Drafting Training Program, akụkụ nke National Youth Administration of Works Progress Administration. Tinyere onye na-ese ihe maka ndị na-ese ụkpụrụ ụlọ abụọ mbụ edebanyere aha na Detroit, Alfonso R

Feliciano (1883 ruo 1940) onye Puerto Rican gụsịrị akwụkwọ na Universidad de Barcelona, na Donald Frank White. Ọ bụ onye na-ahụ maka ihe owuwu maka Ụlọ Ọgwụ Trinity dị na Detroit, ụlọ ọgwụ ojii nke mechiri na 1962.
Parker bụ onye otu Peter Pan Nursery. Ọ na-arụkwa ọrụ na njikọ ndị ọkachamara, gụnyere Alpha Kappa Alpha sorority, National Technical Association, na Detroit Youth Assembly.
